
Algorithm:
Step 1:
Start from the root.

Step 2:
If root is null:
    return null

Step 3:
First recursively remove target leaf nodes from the left subtree:

    root.left = removeLeafNodes(root.left, target)

Step 4:
Then recursively remove target leaf nodes from the right subtree:

    root.right = removeLeafNodes(root.right, target)

Step 5:
After left and right are processed, check current node:

    if root.left == null
    and root.right == null
    and root.val == target

    return null

Step 6:
Otherwise, return root.


Code:
class Solution {
    public TreeNode removeLeafNodes(TreeNode root, int target) {

        // Empty tree
        if (root == null) return null;

        // First clean left and right subtrees
        root.left = removeLeafNodes(root.left, target);
        root.right = removeLeafNodes(root.right, target);

        // Remove current node if it is a target leaf
        if (root.left == null && root.right == null && root.val == target) {
            return null;
        }

        return root;
    }
}
